# Game Data Pipeline

## Source

XML files in `../ChummerGenSR4/bin/data/` (30 core files per `manifestdata.xml`).

## Convert

```bash
npm run convert        # data + custom/override merge + translations
npm run convert:data   # data only
```

Output: `public/data/*.json`, `public/lang/*.json`, `public/manifest.json`

## JSON shape

- Collections unwrap to arrays: `weapons[]` not `{ weapon: [] }`
- Some files have multiple top-level collections (e.g. `weapons.json` also has `accessories`, `mods`)
- Formula strings stay as strings: `"Rating * 3000"`, `"(STR/2+1)P"`, `"8R"`
- Item primary key: `name` (ranges use `category` as display name)

## Reference catalog

`src/app/core/models/data-catalog.ts` — maps browse IDs to `file` + `collectionKey`.

When adding a browse list:
1. Verify collection key in generated JSON
2. Add entry with `group` for index grouping
3. Use `extractCollection()` in `ChummerDataService.loadItems()`

## Custom content

Converter merges `override_*` (replace by name) and `custom_*` (append, skip duplicates), scanning `custom content/` subfolders with `--recursive-custom`.

## Re-convert after changes

If ChummerGenSR4 data updates, re-run `npm run convert` — do not hand-edit `public/data/*.json`.
